This ensures that we are passing things in the correct spots.

Prior to this, the service_signing_name was being passed in in the position of default_endpoint, making it non functional.

@kyleknap

Set DATABASES to multiline form
```
DATABASES = {
    'default':
        {
             'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.postgresql_psycopg2',
             'HOST': 'host',
             'NAME': 'dbname',
             'PASSWORD': 'pwd',
             'PORT': '5432',
             'USER': 'user'
        }
}
```
instead of single line:
```
DATABASES = {
    'default':
        {'NAME': 'dbname', 'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.postgresql_psycopg2', 'PASSWORD': 'pwd', 'PORT': '5432', 'HOST': 'host', 'USER': 'user'}
}
```

